<subSubSection id="C37C6FCF4010FF83FF7BFDA7FADFFA64" pageId="8" pageNumber="389" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF7BFDA7FEEDFDE0" blockId="8.[151,808,510,608]" box="[151,284,582,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FF7BFDA7FEEDFDE0" box="[151,284,582,608]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 6" captionStart-1="FIGURE 7" captionStart-2="FIGURE 8" captionStartId-0="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionStartId-1="10.[151,250,1461,1485]" captionStartId-2="11.[151,250,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,633,1932]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetId-1="figure-24@10.[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetId-2="figure-201@11.[151,1436,633,1932]" captionTargetPageId-0="9" captionTargetPageId-1="10" captionTargetPageId-2="11" captionText-0="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 7. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C. dorsal view; D. second and third abdominal tergites with stridulatory pegs in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in lateral view; F. hind femur in lateral view; G–H. subgenital plate in view." captionText-2="FIGURE 8. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. A–B. male; C–E. female; F. nest." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358432" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358434" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6358432/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6358434/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Figures 6–8</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF7BFD6FFB03FD4D" blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B912E0564010FF83FF7BFD6FFE83FD28" bold="true" box="[151,370,654,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body slightly smaller than other species. Face nearly smooth, with scattered impressed dots and shallow transverse riffles (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FE53FD53FDEBFD4D" box="[447,538,690,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Fastigium verticis wider than scape. Ocelli indistinct (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FB67FD53FB14FD4D" box="[1163,1253,690,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF2BFD37FCA1FC95" blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
Anterior margin of pronotum slightly projected in the middle, posterior margin finely concave (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FAFEFD37FA61FD71" box="[1298,1424,726,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6C–D</figureCitation>
); lateral lobes loner than high, anterior angle rounded (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FD07FD1BFCB2FC95" box="[747,835,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF2BFCFEFC41FC25" blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
Fore coxae swollen, with 1 spine (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FDA4FCFFFD50FCB9" box="[584,673,798,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). Fore and middle femora unarmed on ventral surfaces, hind femora with 6–9 internal and 1–3 external spines on ventral surface. Fore and middle tibiae with 5 pairs of ventral spurs, including 1 pair of apical ones; hind tibiae slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FCD0FC87FC63FC01" box="[828,914,870,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
) with 4–5 internal and 5–6 external spines on dorsal surface, apices with 1 pair of dorsal and 2 pairs of ventral spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF2BFC4FFEA0FBD8" blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
Second and third abdominal tergite with two rows of stridulatory pegs respectively (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FB80FC4FFB33FC49" box="[1132,1218,942,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Eighth abdominal tergite prolonged, curved downwards (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FDA7FC33FD51FC6D" box="[587,672,978,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6F</figureCitation>
). Ninth abdominal tergite split along the midline, terminating into a slender spine on both sides, its apex directing forward and slightly inward (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FC0BFC17FBB3FB91" box="[999,1090,1014,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6H</figureCitation>
). Cerci conical and stout. Subgenital plate with V-shaped concavity on posterior margin, the lateral lobes terminating into a digitate process (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FA83FBFBFF43FBD9" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6I</figureCitation>
). Styli absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF2BFB83FAB0FB45" blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B912E0564010FF83FF2BFB83FED4FBFC" bold="true" box="[199,293,1122,1148]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Female.</emphasis>
Subgenital plate nearly inverted trapezoidal in ventral view, the lateral margins of basal area triangular and curved dorsad, narrowing to apex, posterior margin almost straight with indistinct median concavity (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FAD9FB67FA7EFB20" box="[1333,1423,1158,1184]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1461,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C. dorsal view; D. second and third abdominal tergites with stridulatory pegs in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in lateral view; F. hind femur in lateral view; G–H. subgenital plate in view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358432/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor short and strongly curved upwards, dorsal and ventral margins smooth, apices obtuse (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FB31FB4BFAC5FB45" box="[1245,1332,1194,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1461,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C. dorsal view; D. second and third abdominal tergites with stridulatory pegs in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in lateral view; F. hind femur in lateral view; G–H. subgenital plate in view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358432/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF2BFB2FFADFFA64" blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B912E0564010FF83FF2BFB2FFEBEFB68" bold="true" box="[199,335,1230,1256]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body yellowish brown, Face with 1 vertical stripe along the midline (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FB8DFB2FFB37FB68" box="[1121,1222,1230,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Figs. 6A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FB3DFB2FFB07FB68" box="[1233,1270,1230,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1461,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C. dorsal view; D. second and third abdominal tergites with stridulatory pegs in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in lateral view; F. hind femur in lateral view; G–H. subgenital plate in view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358432/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">7A</figureCitation>
), which reaching dorsal surface of head and then extending to the apex of abdomen, the median band widened to semicircular at posterior margin of head (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FE55FAF7FDFEFAB1" box="[441,527,1302,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) and varying extension at the disc of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FBC1FAF7FB74FAB1" box="[1069,1157,1302,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Genae below eyes with 1 black vertical stripe on each side (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FDC7FADBFD77FAD5" box="[555,646,1338,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Clypeo-frontal suture with 1 pair of black spots (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FB52FADBFAE9FAD5" box="[1214,1304,1338,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Fastigium verticis with 1 black horizontal stripe, behind the stripe with 1 black spot on external side of the median black band (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FF4CFA63FF0BFA1D" box="[160,250,1410,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Eyes black. Internal margin of antennal cavities and scape with black spots. Flagellum black. Maxillary palpi light brown. Anterior and ventral margins of pronotum black (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FC7FFA47FC1DFA41" box="[915,1004,1446,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
). Apical areas of all femora, basal and apical areas of all tibiae, and spines of hind legs black. Apices of spines of ninth abdominal tergite black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
