<subSubSection id="C37C6FCF4010FF83FF2BF927FB01F8A8" pageId="8" pageNumber="389" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF2BF927FB01F8A8" blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B912E0564010FF83FF2BF927FEBDF960" bold="true" box="[199,332,1734,1760]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species differs from congeneric species in: face with 1 longitudinal black stripe along the middle (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FF1AF90BFEA0F884" box="[246,337,1770,1796]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FEB1F90BFE73F884" box="[349,386,1770,1796]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1461,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C. dorsal view; D. second and third abdominal tergites with stridulatory pegs in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in lateral view; F. hind femur in lateral view; G–H. subgenital plate in view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358432/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">7A</figureCitation>
), median black band of pronotal disc narrow, spines of male ninth abdominal tergite slender (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FF4CF8EFFF08F8A9" box="[160,249,1806,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1542]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–D. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C–D. dorsal view; E. hind femur in lateral view; F–I. apex of abdomen: F. lateral view, G. dorsal view, H. apical and ventral view, I. ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 6G</figureCitation>
), female subgenital plate longer than wide with posterior margin slightly arched (
<figureCitation id="135D20C14010FF83FB65F8EFFB12F8A8" box="[1161,1251,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1461,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[151,1436,166,1437]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Apterolarnaca (Bianigryllacris) tenuispinacia sp. nov. Male: A. head in frontal view; B–C. head and pronotum: B. lateral view, C. dorsal view; D. second and third abdominal tergites with stridulatory pegs in lateral view; E. apex of abdomen in lateral view; F. hind femur in lateral view; G–H. subgenital plate in view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358432" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358432/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37C6FCF4010FF82FF2BF8D3FEAAF88C" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="390" pageId="8" pageNumber="389" type="etymology">
<subSubSection id="C37C6FCF4010FF83FF2BF8D3FD1CF8F0" pageId="8" pageNumber="389" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD93C444010FF83FF2BF8D3FD1CF8F0" blockId="8.[151,1437,654,1905]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis id="B912E0564010FF83FF2BF8D3FEBFF8CC" bold="true" box="[199,334,1842,1868]" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name derived from Latin 
<emphasis id="B912E0564010FF83FD98F8D2FD55F8CC" box="[628,676,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">tenu</emphasis>
(tenuous) plus 
<emphasis id="B912E0564010FF83FCA3F8D2FC8FF8CC" box="[847,894,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="389">spin</emphasis>
(spine), referring to the posterior margin of male ninth abdominal tergite with 1 pair of tenuous spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF196CCC4011FF82FF7BF9FCFE14F9FE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6358430" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6358430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6358430/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="390" startId="9.[151,250,1565,1589]" targetBox="[151,1436,218,1542]" targetPageId="9">
